You are working on HYDRA, an AI-powered SOC automation platform.

Read CLAUDE.md at repo root for full project context.

Key rules:
- Go API in api/ — uses Gin framework, package main
- Python worker in worker/ — uses Temporal SDK, psycopg2 for DB
- All database queries must be tenant-scoped (WHERE tenant_id = $X)
- All new migrations go in migrations/ with next sequential number
- Tests: Go in api/*_test.go, Python in worker/tests/test_*.py
- Never hardcode secrets — use env vars from .env.example
- Error responses must use respondInternalError() — never leak details
- LLM calls go through LiteLLM (port 4000), never direct to model
- Sandbox code must pass AST prefilter before execution
- Redis accessed via go-redis/v9 client (api/ratelimit.go), never raw TCP
- DB connections via pooled_connection() context manager (worker/database/pool_manager.py)
- Temporal activities use @activity.defn, workflows use @workflow.defn
- All LLM inputs wrapped with wrap_untrusted_data() for injection defense
